# Cloud media storage

All recordings, images, and videos MUST be stored in cloud object storage (Firebase Storage / GCS).

## Required

- Upload via `StorageService` to cloud bucket
- Persist only object key + URL + mime/size in DB
- Serve via signed URL or cloud stream
- Object keys: `users/{userId}/recordings|images|videos/{id}/{uuid}.ext`

## Forbidden

- Saving media under `src/`, `be/src/`, `fe/src/`
- Using `be/uploads` or local disk as primary storage
- Committing audio/image/video binaries to git
- Controllers calling `fs` / Multer disk `dest` for media

Local filesystem is allowed only as a temporary buffer before cloud upload, never as source of truth.
